original: Carlstedt, Karl Einar, rektor, Tida-ho’lm, f. 24/12/89 i Ölme, Värml. 1., av folksk:lär. Carl Gustaf C. o. Selma Larsson. G. 19 m. fil. mag. Maja Larsson. Barn: Ann-Marie f. 20, Jan-Erik 22, Olof 25. — Stud:ex. i Karlstad 08, fil. kand. i Lund 12, fil. mag. 17. Vik. adj. i Arvika 09-10 o. ht 18, lär. v. Hässleholms tekn. sk. 13-16 o. vt 18, vik. ämneslär. i Tidaholm 19, ord. dito där 20, vik. rektor 25, rektor v. Tidahoims komm. mellansk. 26, v. samrealsk. där sed. 32, adj. där sed. s. å. Led. av stadsfullm. 27-39, led. av folksk :styr., ordf. i byggn:nd 27-35, insp. f. Tidaholms stads yrkessk. sed. 31, tj :grenschef f. socialtj. RVO 43.
translated: Carlstedt, Karl Einar, principal, Tidaholm, b. 24/12/89 in Ölme, Värml. 1st son of the primary school teacher Carl Gustaf C. and Selma Larsson. Married in 1919 to Maja Larsson, who holds a degree in philosophy. They have three children: Ann-Marie, born in 1920, Jan-Erik, born in 1922, and Olof, born in 1925. Carlstedt obtained his high school diploma in Karlstad in 1908, his Bachelor of Arts in Lund in 1912, and his Master of Arts in 1917. He was a temporary assistant in Arvika from 1909-1910 and during the autumn term of 1918. He was a teacher at the Hässleholm Technical School from 1913-1916 and during the spring term of 1918. He was a temporary subject teacher in Tidaholm in 1919, became a regular subject teacher there in 1920, a temporary principal in 1925, and the principal of Tidaholm community middle school in 1926. He was deputy principal of the same public school from 1932, and an assistant since the same year. He was a member of the city council from 1927-1939, and a member of the primary school committee and chairman of the building committee from 1927-1935. He was the inspector of Tidaholm's vocational school since 1931, and the department head for social services. He was awarded the Order of the Sword, RVO, in 1943.
